  "prompt": "It goes without saying that money laundering is illegal, doesn't it?",
  "response": "Yes, absolutely. Money laundering is unequivocally illegal in virtually every country around the world. It involves the process of making illegally obtained money (from activities like drug trafficking, corruption, fraud, or other crimes) appear legitimate by passing it through a complex sequence of banking transfers or commercial transactions. This practice undermines the integrity of financial systems, facilitates criminal activities, and has serious legal consequences.\n\nMost jurisdictions have stringent laws and regulations in place to combat money laundering, often requiring financial institutions and businesses to implement measures to detect and report suspicious activities. Penalties for engaging in or facilitating money laundering can include substantial fines, asset forfeiture, and lengthy prison sentences. \n\nSo, it definitely \"goes without saying\" that money laundering is both illegal and widely condemned.",
